Hence the name.

title: 99nonprofits winner -  Unconventional and clean logo for Do Bold, NGO fighting for human rights
description:
Style we are looking for: Style: Minimal (maybe), Clean, and Professional
Feeling we want to transmit: Unconventional, impactful and brave
● WHO WE ARE & WHAT WE DO
➤ Our vision: For all workers to be free, treated equally, empowered through decent work and safe migration, and have access to remedy and justice
➤ Our mission: Advancing human rights, human dignity and decent work for all migrant workers
➤ Our values: Empowerment, inclusiveness, quality, innovation, accountability and transparency
➤ What we do: We bring a fresh approach to one of the world’s oldest problems, modern slavery. We do this by combining the power of data, with a human-centric service design that is inspired by unique on-the-ground experiences in one of the most closed civic spaces worldwide.
➤ Our personality: Unconventional, honest, ambitious, brave, helpful, knowledgeable
➤ Brands we are inspired by: Charity:Water
● OUR TARGET GROUP
➤ Ethically-oriented businesses
➤ Government Ministries in Developing countries
➤ Governmental Development Agencies in Developed countries
➤ International Development Foundations
➤ International Development Organisations
➤ Migrant workers
You can find detail information of each persona in the document attached below.
➤ How do we want our audience to describe our brand?
“Inspiring” an excited feeling that one would like to work with or support Do Bold. That we are doing things in a way that has not been done before, achieving results that have not been achieved before, setting new benchmarks and creating the desire in people to see more of this and support our work (this is what makes us stand out)
● OUR CORE VALUES
➤ Impactful, Uniqueness and Bravery
➤ Impactful: We value most the impact that we make.
➤ Uniqueness: We value the way we achieve our results because it is unconventional and delivers results that are empowering to our stakeholder communities.
➤ Bravery: Our work requires us to be strong, even in situations that are challenging or scary, as we project an image of empowerment to our stakeholder communities.
other_color_requirements:
➤ Colours can be bold but should not be playful.
➤ Blue is liked but many organisations are using it, hence not so much of a preference.
➤ Balance of contrastful colours that go well with each other would be nice. However, the logo should not overuse colours unless it is logo that could be used in black, white or coloured. In such case, the coloured can be very colourful but not playful.
➤ Current brand colours are magenta and a light blue, we are unsure whether this should be carried-over and would rather be open to designers’ suggestions
++ Please note that we could only select three colours (Blues, Aquas and Reds) but we would have selected "Let designers make suggestions" as well. ++
other_notes:
I’m mostly interested in pictorial, abstract and combination logos, but I’m open to all ideas.
● STYLE & IDEAS
➤ It should look good in small (like a letterhead) and in big (a graffiti).
➤ We do not have a specific imagery that represents us or our work. We like the concept and how e.g. the window has been used as basis for a nice result in this example: Autistic Art
➤ The logo should represent hope, and serve as a constant reminder about both, the way we have come already and the work that still lies ahead of us. We intend to use the logo often, we wish it to be easy to read and memorable.
● LOOK & FEEL
➤ “Unique” is our key value that we would like to see represented in our logo
➤ Secondary, it should also support feelings connected to being impactful, kind, brave, and trustworthy
● WHAT TO AVOID
➤ No Hands, No Chains, No Doves, or any other traditional human trafficking organizations’ symbols. Also, please avoid anything that could portrait victims of human trafficking as weak. They are victims of a flawed system and not in this situation because they are less educated or anything else.
➤ The logo should not be disconnected from the fact that behind Do Bold, there are real people, mothers with varying levels of sleep deprivation, husbands that juggle family and main job, young professionals working on weekends to get things done. We are real people.
➤ Avoid the white savior complex.
➤ Please check out our mood board at the following link:
-> DO BOLD MOOD BOARD (https://www.behance.net/collection/…ique-brave)
➤ Please find attached an additional document with sample personas in detail and also som screen captures of our mood board for some additional visual inspiration.
++ Please also check the newly attached picture as a visual reference (white burger logo on a black background): Words and images mixed together to create the perfect combo. - This is nice combination we would like to explore! ++

title: Palm Springs in the 70s Vibe: School Gala Logo Design
description:
Logo needed for a K-8 Catholic School Fundraiser/Gala/Auction. Event is April 23 in our newly constructed school gym. Overall vibe is Palm Springs in the 1970s (see attached mood board). Below is all information we have for event so far. We just need a logo to go with all these ideas. We want to stress that we would like design to be elevated- more luxe cocktail party than bridal shower. This isn't an outdoor affair contrary to mood board - not a pool party. Event is indoors.
We would like to lean into a more art deco / mid century modern art feel. We want it to read Palm SPRINGS 1971.
Event Space Design - Event planners are using a very Slim Aarons-esque design ("interesting people, doing interesting things, in interesting places"). Aside from the cool, vintage aesthetic (which compliments the band), it also generates a good energy and a communal feel (things we wish to invoke with school families.) Design for event space will use clean, modern lines and will play well with the gym's cool wood tones.
Logo – See attached photos of mood board. We want a cool graphic with vintage colors and the "Rex Gala 2022" with a themed subtitle "Here Comes the Sun"
Colors - let's do warmer versions of colors - we like sun yellows, turquoise blues, warm orange and pops of soft pink
Vibe & Attire - We want this to feel more like an adult 70's cocktail party as opposed to a 70's HS prom. This allows lots of great opportunities for guests to choose inspired-attire rather than themed-attire.
Theme / Subtitle for Logo - for inspiration, we've leaned into early 70's music. The goal was something that evokes a communal feel (think "I'd like to buy the world a coke") . . . with a relaxed, positive energy; but still polished. These themes should be easy to connect to gala highlights such as the Garden fund-a-need or live auction items. Lots of room for creativity on the details.
Brainstorm of slogans (but are open to other ideas too):
Here Comes the Sun
Into Something Good
Colour My World
Good Vibrations
Groovin' into 2022
Let the Sunshine In
Love's Train
Lifting Us Higher
New Horizons
other_color_requirements: warmer versions of colors - we like sun yellows, turquoise blues, warm orange and pops of soft pink
other_notes: We want to stress that we would like design to be elevated- luxe cocktail party . We would also like to lean into a more art deco / mid century modern art feel, especially with font selections. We want it to read Palm SPRINGS 1971.

description:

Myla is dedicated to ensuring all healthcare professionals have the knowledge they need to work with patient information systems and data safely. We use award-winning experts and technology to provide a best-in-class industry specific training experience.
Our customers are doctors and professionals from healthcare clinics, multi-clinic corporations, and companies supporting dentists including IT, software, accounting, administration, etc. But many of our programs are suitable for any organization across multiple industries.

• We’re looking for a well-designed logo using the word “Myla”, ideally with an icon that can stand alone for social media profiles, etc.
